r=e^θ 
(
0 ≤ θ ≤ 2π.)
n 
r=\sqrt{x^2+y^2}
\theta=\arctan \frac yx
x,
\sqrt{x^2+y^2}=e^{\arctan \frac yx}
\frac{x+y\frac{dy}{dx}}{\sqrt{x^2+y^2}}
=e^{\arctan \frac yx}\cdot\frac1{1+\left(\frac yx\right)^2}\cdot\frac{\left(x\frac{dy}{dx}-y\right)}{x^2}
=\sqrt{x^2+y^2}\frac{\left(x\frac{dy}{dx}-y\right)}{x^2+y^2} \text { as } e^{\arctan \frac yx}=\sqrt{x^2+y^2}
\implies  \frac{x+y\frac{dy}{dx}}{\sqrt{x^2+y^2}}=\sqrt{x^2+y^2}\frac{\left(x\frac{dy}{dx}-y\right)}{x^2+y^2}
\implies \frac{dy}{dx}=\frac{x+y}{x-y}
\frac{dy}{dx}=0\implies x+y=0\implies \theta=\arctan (-1)=n\pi-\frac{\pi}4
n
0\le \theta\le 2\pi,n=1,2
\frac{dx}{dy}=0\implies x-y=0\implies \theta=\arctan (1)=m\pi+\frac{\pi}4
m
0\le \theta\le 2\pi,m=0,1
y=e^\theta\sin\theta
x=e^\theta\cos\theta
\frac{dy}{dx}=\frac{\frac{dy}{d\theta}}{\frac{dx}{d\theta}}=\frac{\sin\theta +\cos\theta}{\cos\theta - \sin\theta }
0
\theta=7\pi/4,3\pi/4
0
\theta=\pi/4, 5\pi/4
